article.description: Gary Flowers scored 17 points and Southern Mississippi avoided another late-game letdown by defeating SMU 56-53 on Tuesday night.
article.headline: SMU rallies from 10 down late, but can't get past Southern Miss
article.linkText: SMU's rally vs. Southern Miss comes up short
article.story: HATTIESBURG, Miss. -- Gary Flowers scored 17 points and Southern Mississippi avoided another late-game letdown by defeating SMU 56-53 on Tuesday night. Trailing by 10 points with just over a minute left, SMU (10-11, 3-4 Conference USA) mounted a rally to cut the lead to 54-53 with 10 seconds left. But a pair of free throws by Angelo Johnson gave Southern Miss (13-8, 3-4) its final lead, as SMU's Derek Williams missed an off-balance 3-point shot as time expired. Williams scored 24 points, but had a team-high five turnovers. The Mustangs committed 14 turnovers and had just seven assists. The loss snapped a four-game winning streak for SMU, and gave Southern Miss its third straight win against a Conference USA opponent.
